title.narrative: HEALTH SYSTEM STRENGHTENING

description.narrative: Output 2.1. Healthcare professionals have the capacity to provide quality perinatal, modern home visiting and adolescent-friendly services to the most disadvantaged boys and girls, which contributes to Child Health, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, disadvantaged children have equitable access to health and education services to survive, learn, develop and contribute to resilient, inclusive and sustainable communities

description.narrative: Within COVAX, UNICEF facilitated the logistics for 1,177,440 COVID-19 vaccines and an additional 3,240,200 doses of vaccine through procurement services, domestic financing and other donors. In 2021, 3,000 members of 952 Village Health Committees (VHCs) raised awareness on vaccination. They improved the Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission (PMTCT) of HIV and the childcare practices of parents and caregivers, reaching more than 80,000 parents and community members on appropriate childcare practices, the importance of home visiting and COVID-19 preventive measures.A national telemedicine platform was launched with 100 family doctors and 15 specialised doctors from higher health-care levels. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
